parameters:
Mediator Vrebo: I wonder if there's a beautiful lady who is
suitable to be a dancer.

Mediator Vrepo: So, who's going to participate? Due to the
limited slots, only one person can participate.
Mediator Vrepo: Let me know when you're ready.
Mediator Vrepo: Alright, let me guide you.
Mediator Vrebo: You guys are always welcome here.

Mediator Vrepo: What's going on...? Who are these young
ladies?

Clea: I heard that if I ask you, I can become a dancer at
the theater.

Mediator Vrepo: I don't know if you're adventurers in need
of money, but beautiful ladies like you are very welcome.

Mediator Vrepo (This blonde girl... with the atmosphere of
cohabiting with both a young girl and a woman, she has the
potential to be a top dancer with her strong-willed
appearance!)

Mediator Vrepo (I don't understand the ornament on her head,
but her timid atmosphere is charming. Her imposing physique,
which is not suitable for her spiritual nature, is
impressive.)

Mediator Vrepo (A born seductress... I can feel an aura that
surpasses all previous dancers...!)
Mediator Vrepo: So, are you here to help?

Mage Relm: How rude...! If you have something to say,
please say it!

Mediator Vrepo: So, who's going to participate? Due to the
limited slots, only one person can participate.
Mediator Vrepo: Let me know when you're ready.
Mediator Vrepo: Alright, let me show you around.

Gentleman Kabaji: I really appreciate your help. If you
don't mind, please accept this as well.

Priestess Sophia: I pray for the success of the winery. May
we receive the blessings of the goddess Imiserinos.

Clea: They seemed like a close couple. It reminds me of my
father and mother...

Priestess Sophia: Yes, that's right... being able to always
be together with the person you love...

Priestess Sophia: There is no greater happiness than
that...
Clea: Sophia-san, your complexion... Are you okay?

Priestess Sophia: Yes, I'm fine... I just had a beautiful
dream...

Priestess Sophia: It's just that it's so beautiful... I'm
just bewildered by the reality in front of me...
Priestess Sophia: I will wake up completely soon...
Is there something you need, miss?
Priestess Sophia: I came to talk about the wine matter.

Gentleman Kabaji: As Cors-san said, it seems that your
request will probably be resolved by the women.
Gentleman Kabaji: Let's talk about the details right away.

Gentleman Kabaji: I used to run a large winery, but before
the war in the neighboring country Tarasa, I switched my
business to distributing supplies.

Gentleman Kabaji: It's a job that supports the Imperial
Army's logistics. I have been very successful and live a
comfortable life.

Priestess Sophia: Um, is it about time we get to the main
topic?

Gentleman Kabaji: Excuse me. As one gets older, they tend
to talk more... The request is to have you bid on wine at an
auction.
Gentleman Kabaji: Do you know about Deirei's right eye?
Clea: Do you know about it?

Priestess Sophia: The wine that was said to be a miracle...
But it shouldn't be something that is put up for auction.

Gentleman Kabaji: It can definitely be put up for auction
because my wife put it up for auction.

Gentleman Kabaji: I don't intend to blame my wife for
getting tired of my nostalgia for the past... I just want it
to be recovered.
Priestess Sophia: Can't you go yourself?

Gentleman Kabaji: My wife cries every day with regret... I
want to be by her side now.

Gentleman Kabaji: Since I have gained the trust of Mr.
Cors, who supports the Imperial Army's logistics, I will
also trust you and entrust you with 50,000G.
Clea: T-This is an enormous amount of money...!

Gentleman Kabaji: The Fotizona Port is the auction venue.
Please grant the wish of this elderly person who doesn't
have much time left!
Priestess Sophia: Understood, leave it to me.
Gentleman Kabaji: Please take care of us as a couple.
Cleric Sophia: This will be the right eye of Delia.

Gentleman Kabaji: As expected, it was the right decision
to rely on all of you! Now, here is the promised reward.

Cleric Sophia: It is an honor to be involved with such
wonderful wine. Unfortunately, I can only watch.
Gentleman Kabaji: Do you want to drink this wine?

Cleric Sophia: It's just a joke... Please don't take it
seriously!

Gentleman Kabaji: This wine, a masterpiece created by
chance... It has been a curse to me.

Gentleman Kabaji: I had forgotten the joy of creating a
masterpiece, a glorious past that cannot be surpassed, which
is making wine.

Gentleman Kabaji: I have decided to start a winery again,
thanks to all of you for helping me regain my
determination.
Cleric Sophia: Yes, I think it's a wonderful goal.
Gentleman Kabaji: Now, to a wonderful encounter!
Cleric Sophia: To the glory of wonderful wine!
Clea: It has a complex flavor, doesn't it...
Thief Nora: Ugh... It's so bitter...!

Mage Relm: Everyone is like a child! The greatness of this
wine... *burp*!

Gentleman Kabaji: Hahaha, please don't force yourself.
Originally, it's meant to be diluted with water before
drinking.

Cleric Sophia: A definite sweetness within the
bitterness... This is the miraculous wine... It has a
wonderful flavor.

Gentleman Kabaji: Just like life, it has both bitterness
and sweetness... That's what makes it interesting.

Gentleman Kabaji: As we grow older, our words tend to
sound preachy. Today, everything is on me, so please feel
free, everyone!
Cleric Sophia: Hic...! Ah, today is the best day ever!
Cleric Sophia: Now, please drink more as well!

Young Man Rooshi: You've had too much to drink! Your
companion has already gone back to the room, you know?

Cleric Sophia: Hehehe, the adult time is far from over! But
my, it's quite hot in here... *hic*

Young Man Rooshi: Please don't undress! Ahh, come on, I'll
take you back to the room!

Gentleman Kabaji: Everyone, it's been a while since we last
met!
Clea: Long time no see! You look well, and that's great.

Gentleman Kabaji: I bought back a part of the winery I
sold. Now I'm struggling with my wife to deal with the
grapes.
Gentleman Kabaji: Actually, I wanted to meet all of you!

Clea: This is a really beautiful color. Did Mr. Kabaji make
this?
Gentleman Kabaji: Yes, I imagined all of you.

Gentleman Kabaji: As soon as I heard the rumors of the
Empire's hero, the Dragon Slayer, I was convinced it was all
of you.

Gentleman Kabaji: This wine doesn't have a name. What do
you think? Do you have any good suggestions?

Clea: How about Sophia? When it comes to wine among us,
it's synonymous with Sophia.

Gentleman Kabaji: Hahaha, that's wonderful. May I have your
name?
Priestess Sophia: Um, um, if it's alright with me...

Gentleman Kabaji: I see, so it's a specialty of the tavern.
If it's alright with you, how about the new creation called
Sophia?

Thief Nora: With this, Mr. Gala will definitely be
pleased!

Gentleman Kabaji: Since I only have one bottle on hand,
would you mind coming to my winery?

Mage Relm: Sophia-san, it's great that we have wine that
not only we can drink, but even swim in!

Clea: You seem unwell. Let's go to the winery just the two
of us.

Clea: Sophia-san, please rest at the inn. Once we finish
collecting the wine, we will come to the inn.
Priestess Sophia: Oh, thank you for your concern.

Priestess Sophia: Mr. Kabaji, please take good care of your
wife.

Gentleman Kabaji: Yes, of course, I love my wife more than
anyone else.

Priestess Sophia: Hic... Ugh... A wine named after me...
Hic...

Priestess Sophia: I don't have any qualifications for
something like that... Someone like me... hic...

Priestess Sophia: When I come here, it reminds me... of
that person who did nothing wrong... *sigh* I...
Innkeeper: Customers, please return to your rooms soon.
Innkeeper: Hey, can you hear me properly?
Innkeeper: The customer seems to have passed out...
Innkeeper: So, what will you do today?

Regular Customer: You're quite enthusiastic about your side
job, huh? Haha, be careful not to catch the attention of
that Cors guy, okay?

Innkeeper: Don't make too much of a fuss in the room at the
very back, okay?
Young Man Rooshi: Hello, have a nice day.
Male Sailor: Are you taking a break too, miss?

Sailor Man: The young one who used to come here often is
gone. Meeting and parting... I suppose this is the fate of a
port town...
Innkeeper: If you're not ordering anything, please leave.
Innkeeper: So, what would you like to order?

Clea: Please tell me the location of the Great Rock
Castle.

Innkeeper: I've been asked that question just now. I'll
tell you the location, but I recommend you to be cautious.

Innkeeper: No one has come back after asking that
question.

\CL Area Liberation\c[18]\CL Mycos Region/Great Rock
Castle\c[0]
Innkeeper: If you're not ordering anything, please leave.

Bar Staff: It's troublesome when customers touch without
leaving a tip.

Master Gambler: Mucos is a shipwright where various people
gather, including sailors, mercenaries, and merchants. The
gambler in front of us is also one of them.

Expert Gambler: Miss... would you like to play a game of
High and Low with me?
Will you pay 20,000G to play High and Low?
Expert Gambler: Drawing cards is also a skill.

Expert Gambler: It seems like I can have a fun match after
a long time.

Expert Gambler: It reminded me of the time I was swept away
by Cors after a good match.

Expert Gambler: Don't think about making money with this
strange business of mine, where I take all the bets, okay?

Expert Gambler: I'm sorry, but I don't play games without
betting money.

Cors the Wanderer: I'm grateful that you're willing to take
on this request. This time, we need a strong-willed woman
who can handle herself.
Clea: Please tell me the details.

Cors the Wanderer: A while ago, there was a defector from
our organization who fled to a rival organization.

Cors the Wanderer: He's a man with a strong sense of
caution, but there's a certain hobby of his that he won't be
able to resist for much longer.

Sophia the Priestess: A certain hobby... Oh my, does it
have a naughty feel to it?

Cors the Wanderer: As expected, you have a good intuition.
Actually, this man is a big fan of stripping, you know.

Cors the Wanderer: There's a possibility that he'll come
soon.

Sophia the Priestess: If that's the case, wouldn't it be
better for everyone to handle it? After all, Mucos isn't
your territory, right?

Cors the Wanderer: In the past, there have been repeated
conflicts, and the underground illegal bars are considered
off-limits.

Cors the Wanderer: So, I would like all of you to
infiltrate and capture a man with a knife tattoo.
Clea: Won't we be suspected as female customers?

Priestess Sophia: Hehe, Clea-chan, we will infiltrate as
dancers.
Priestess Sophia: That's what you mean, right?

Mage Relm: Absolutely not! Why do we have to imitate
something like that!

Thief Nora: I don't know about being a dancer, but is it
really that scary!?

Cors the Wanderer: Being a dancer is the only way to enter
the illegal bar without arousing suspicion, you know.

Cors the Wanderer: Please, I beg of you! If you can
complete this request, I will assist you when you are in
need.
Clea: Understood... I will accept the request.

Cors the Wanderer: As expected of the Adventurer Guild's
rising star! I believe there might be a fight when capturing
the man, so please be careful.

Mage Relm: N-No way...! I absolutely won't become a dancer,
you know!

Thief Nora: I-I would prefer to p-pass if possible...
ahaha

Cors the Wanderer: Only one person can participate as a
dancer. Here are the dancer outfits that seem to suit all of
you.

Cors the Wanderer: When you're ready, please talk to the
intermediary man here.

Cors the Wanderer: Thanks to you, we were able to safely
secure the tattooed man for the organization.
Clea: With this, the request is complete, right?

Cors the Wanderer: The intermediary Vrepo seems to have
taken a liking to all of you. If you're interested, how
about becoming a dancer for real instead of just
infiltrating?
Clea: I am an adventurer, so... excuse me.

Cors the Wanderer: It's just a light joke, but if you're
interested, we're recruiting on the bulletin board, so feel
free to join.

Cors the Wanderer: Here is your reward and a personal thank
you as well. If there are any more special jobs, please feel
free to let me know.

Traveling goods merchant: 'Mycos is a charming town. The
unruly and tense atmosphere is absolutely fantastic.'
